            <ol>
                <li>Travellers to the country should start their trip by spending a few days in its most famous city, Dhaka, which also serves as the capital of the country. The largest city of Bangladesh is home to many beautiful spots such as National Parliament House, Ahsan Manzil in Old Dhaka, Curzon Hall in the University of Dhaka, Lalbagh Fort and the Independence Monument in Suhrawardy Udyan. </li>
                <li>Next, travellers should head over to the Chittagong which is the second largest city in the country owing to its location on the shores of the Bay of Bengal which has facilitated the development of the Port of Chittagong. The important city is home to other tourist destinations Chittagong War Cemetery, Patenga, Foy’s Lake, Jamboree Park and Shah Amanat Bridge. </li>
                <li>Travellers will also enjoy various other sites located here such as the historical temples, mosques Buddhist monasteries and remains of palaces and archaeological sites. The natural beauty of Bangladesh is also worth noting given its long unbroken beach, Cox’s Bazaar, the mangrove forests in Sunderban, the Chittagong Hill Tracts and the tea gardens of Sylhet. </li>
