            <h2>Where To Land In Bangladesh? </h2>
            <p>The most important airport of Bangladesh is the Hazrat Shahjalal International Airport Dhaka which is located in the Kurmitola region at a distance of seventeen kilometres or eleven miles from the city centre. The airport, known in previous times as Zia International Airport and Dacca International Airport, provides services to over six million passengers travelling to and from the city every year. The current name of the airport is intended as a tribute to Shah Jalal who is a respected Sufi saint of the country. </p>
            <p>The other important airport of Bangladesh which receives international flights is the Osmani International Airport, Sylhet which is located on the Airport Road in the Sylhet city of the Sylhet district of the Sylhet division of the country. The airport provides services to over six hundred and thirty-four thousand passengers travelling to and from the city every year. </p>
